
[1]novitiate

   NOVI'TIATE, n.

   1. The state or time or learning rudiments.

   2. In religious houses, a year or other time of probation for the trial
   of a noveice, to determine whether he has the necessary qualities for
   living up to the rule to which his vow is to bind him.
